words.definition: To cause the death of a person, animal, or living thing.
words.example: He tried to kill the bug.

words.definition: To continue to exist, especially after other similar people or things have ceased to do so.
words.example: Only a few cookies remain.

words.definition: Of high quality; satisfactory; a sum of money exacted as a penalty.
words.example: The weather is fine. He paid a fine for speeding.

words.definition: Having previously filled a particular role or been a particular thing.
words.example: The former president gave a speech.

words.definition: Important, serious, or significant; a military rank or a field of study.
words.example: This is a major problem. She is a biology major.

words.definition: Required to be done, achieved, or present; needed; essential.
words.example: Water is necessary for life.

words.definition: To cause to go or be taken to a particular destination.
words.example: Send me an email.

words.definition: To think or believe that something will happen or that someone will do something.
words.example: I expect you to be on time.

words.definition: A faculty by which the body perceives an external stimulus.
words.example: She has a good sense of smell.

words.definition: To construct by putting parts or materials together.
words.example: They will build a house.

words.definition: To remain in the same place.
words.example: Please stay here.

words.definition: To move downward, typically rapidly and freely without control; a decrease.
words.example: Be careful not to fall. There was a fall in prices.

words.definition: Used to express a range of emotions including surprise, realization, and disappointment.
words.example: Oh, I didn't know that!

words.definition: A large body of people united by common descent, history, culture, or language, inhabiting a particular country or territory.
words.example: Canada is a nation.

words.definition: A detailed proposal for doing or achieving something; to decide on and arrange in advance.
words.example: What's your plan for tomorrow? Plan your work carefully.

words.definition: To make an opening, incision, or wound in something.
words.example: Cut the paper with scissors.

words.definition: An educational institution or establishment, in particular one providing higher education or specialized professional or vocational training.
words.example: She goes to college in New York.

words.definition: The feeling of wanting to know or learn about something; to attract the attention of.
words.example: She has an interest in music. Does this interest you?

words.definition: The end of the life of a person or organism.
words.example: They mourned her death.

words.definition: A series of lessons or lectures in a particular subject; the route or direction followed by something.
words.example: She is taking a math course.

words.definition: An unknown or unspecified person.
words.example: Someone is at the door.

words.definition: Practical contact with and observation of facts or events; to encounter or undergo.
words.example: She has a lot of experience. Experience the beauty of nature.

words.definition: At or to the back of; in support of.
words.example: The cat is behind the sofa.

words.definition: To arrive at; to stretch out an arm in a specified direction.
words.example: Can you reach the shelf?

words.definition: Relating to a particular area or neighborhood.
words.example: Buy from local shops.

words.definition: The number 5.
words.example: There are five apples.

words.definition: To perform duties or services for another person or an organization.
words.example: They serve lunch at noon.

words.definition: To bear all or part of the weight of; to give assistance to.
words.example: I support your decision. The bridge needs support.

words.definition: A thing that happens, especially one of importance.
words.example: The event was a success.

words.definition: Relating to an authority or public body; a person holding public office.
words.example: It's an official document. The official made an announcement.

words.definition: Belonging to or associated with which person.
words.example: Whose book is this?

words.definition: A subject or situation under consideration; to be important.
words.example: It's a serious matter. It doesn't matter.

words.definition: Every person.
words.example: Everyone is welcome.

words.definition: The middle point of something; to place in the middle.
words.example: The table is in the center of the room. Center the text.

words.definition: Two individuals of the same sort considered together; two people who are married, engaged, or otherwise closely associated.
words.example: A happy couple walked by.

words.definition: An area of ground on which a town, building, or monument is constructed.
words.example: This is the site of the new school.
